Defaults value 'analyte' NULL. metabolite Observation metabolite, logical. cmt compartment observation numeric. subject_filter filtering apply DM domain. observation_filter filtering apply observation source data. TESTCD_field xxTESTCD field. Defaults two-character domain name followed 'TESTCD', NULL. DTC_field field use date-time code observation. Defaults two-character domain name followed 'DTC', NULL. Allowed values "TPT" "ELTM".Defaults xxTPT xx domain name, NULL. keep Columns keep, character. include_day_in_ntime logical. silent Suppress messages, logical. Defaults nif_option setting NULL.

Auto-generate nif from sdtm object — nif_auto
text: mapping provided, nif_auto() try find matching treatment names EX PCTESTCD PC create basic nif object pharmacokinetic observations. fail EXTRT PCTESTCD identical names found. one mappings provided additional parameters, nif_auto() create respective observations. Mappings must provided form: TESTCD ~ EXTRT TESTCD can xxTESTCD domain xx included sdtm object. See testcd() overview analytes domains. Formulae can also specify multiple observations associated one treatment, e.g., RS2023 + RS2023487A ~ EXAMPLINIB. Multiple mappings can given, separated commas. analyte name nif object automatically set respective TESTCD. IMPORTANT: multiple analytes specified treatment, implicitly assumed first analyte corresponds parent analyte treatment, e.g., case , 'RS2023' assumed analyte 'EXAMPLINIB' treatment parent compound. Note compartments (CMT) automatically assigned. control compartments, analyte names parent assignment desired, stepwise creation nif object using add_administration() add_observation() recommended.
